.TH MAKNOON 1 "April 2026" "1.0.0" "Maknoon Manual"
.SH NAME
maknoon \- Versatile, ultra-efficient Post-Quantum CLI encryption tool.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B maknoon
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIflags\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Maknoon (مكنون) is a high-performance encryption tool designed for a post-quantum world. 
It utilizes ML-KEM (Kyber) for encryption, ML-DSA (Dilithium) for signatures, and XChaCha20-Poly1305 for streaming data integrity.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B keygen
Generate a full Post-Quantum identity (Encryption + Signing keys).
.TP
.B encrypt [file/dir]
Encrypt a file or directory. Supports --compress and --public-key.
.TP
.B decrypt [file]
Decrypt and restore data. Automatically detects archive and compression status.
.TP
.B sign [file]
Generate a detached Post-Quantum signature for a file.
.TP
.B verify [file]
Cryptographically verify a file's integrity and origin.
.TP
.B vault
Manage a secure, encrypted password database.
.TP
.B gen
Generate high-entropy secure passwords or passphrases.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-p, \-\-public-key
Path to a recipient's public key (.kem.pub or .sig.pub).
.TP
.B \-k, \-\-private-key
Path to your private key (.kem.key or .sig.key).
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-passphrase
Provide a passphrase non-interactively.
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-compress
Enable Zstd compression before encryption.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.maknoon/keys/
Default directory for storing cryptographic identities.
.TP
.I ~/.maknoon/vaults/
Default directory for password databases.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MAKNOON_PASSPHRASE
A passphrase used to unlock keys and vaults non-interactively.
.SH AUTHOR
Ahmed Abdelaal
.SH SEE ALSO
